{"key":"post-15460046","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15460046</id>\n<content>The temperature on the AA75x is maintained by the thermostat.&amp;nbsp; The mechanical timer only rings a bell, but does not shut the unit off.&amp;nbsp; Once you bleed steam and shut the toggle valve, it becomes set and forget until it's time to shut off.&amp;nbsp; Actually, I hate the term 'set and forget' because it implies you shouldn't monitor the unit during operation, which you should.&amp;nbsp; Equipment fails and you should never leave it unattended.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't expect to put 27 quart jars in the 75X.&amp;nbsp; I think it holds 16 or something close to that, but I don't use jars any more..&amp;nbsp; You can sterilize 27 quarts of grain, provided you use filter patch bags.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can also can in the 75X, but have to be there to release the toggle valve as soon as pressure reaches zero on cool down.&amp;nbsp; I have 4 of them.&amp;nbsp; You can get a cool cart to roll them on from U-line.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/11-005/701402201-AA-75X_on_cart.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/11-005/701402201-thumb_AA-75X_on_cart.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15460575</next>\n<prev>15459491</prev>\n<first>15458551</first>\n<last>15460575</last>\n<when>1322956144</when>\n<utime>12/04/11 01:49 AM</utime>\n</post>"}